  "texts": [
    "However, decision trees, when used in isolation, tend to overfit the training data.",
    "To address this issue and prevent overfitting, random forest models are typically constructed by aggregating multiple decision trees or through regularization techniques 66, 74.",
    "An illustration of the RF process is shown in Fig. 11.",
    "First, the size of the samples is established, and then each sample has a decision tree constructed for it.",
    "Based on the input parameters entered, each decision tree generates a prediction."
  ]
}